      <h1 class='title'>Iraq: Service Police Investigations</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='lords-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 04 February 2005 vol 669 cc21-2WS</cite>
      
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_21ws' title='Col. 21WS &mdash; HL Deb 04 February 2005 vol 669 c21WS' name='column_21ws' href='#column_21ws' rel='bookmark'>21WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0669P0-04667'>
        <a name='S5LV0669P0_20050204_LWS_1'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-peter-goldsmith' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0669P0_20050204_LWS_1' title='Link to this speech by Mr Peter Goldsmith' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-peter-goldsmith" title="Mr Peter Goldsmith">The Attorney-General (Lord Goldsmith)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0669P0-04667">Further to my Statement on 3 February 2005<span class="italic">(Official</span>
          <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_22ws' title='Col. 22WS &mdash; HL Deb 04 February 2005 vol 669 c22WS' name='column_22ws' href='#column_22ws' rel='bookmark'>22WS</a>
          <span class="italic">Report,</span> col. <span class="italic">WS 17),</span> two additional individuals have now been told of the charges they face. They are:</p><p id="S5LV0669P0-04668">Private Samuel May of 3rd Battalion the Parachute Regiment; and</p><p id="S5LV0669P0-04669">Roberto Di-Gregorio, former member of the same regiment (now a civilian).</p><p id="S5LV0669P0-04670">The charges relate to an incident which allegedly took place on 11 May 2003 in Al U'Zayra in southern Iraq.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
